entries.title: Burkina Faso Tells French Troops to Leave
entries.description: The West African nation’s decision is the latest blow to Europe’s presence in the troubled Sahel region, where Russia is gaining influence.

entries.title: Janet Yellen Pushes China on Debt Relief for Zambia
entries.description: The Treasury secretary, during a three-country trip to Africa, pursued a crucial test of a U.S.-backed effort to help developing countries.

entries.title: Germany, France Back EU Push to Counter U.S. Subsidies
entries.description: Their support increases the likelihood that the bloc can agree on simpler regulation and additional aid for specific sectors in response to Washington’s Inflation Reduction Act.

entries.title: Ukrainians Target Pushkin in Drive Against Russian Influence
entries.description: Ukrainians are taking aim at the symbols of Russian cultural dominance that Moscow spread during centuries of rule over territory that now makes up much of their country.

entries.title: New Zealand's Tourism Rebound Strains Labor Market
entries.description: A faster-than-expected recovery in travel adds to price pressures in the South Pacific country, where labor markets are tight.

entries.title: Israel's Judicial Reforms Could Strengthen Religion's Role in Public Life
entries.description: The overhaul would allow Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s conservative allies to pass laws granting ultra-Orthodox Jews a legal exemption from military service and permitting gender segregation in public spaces.

entries.title: Iraq's Prime Minister Dismisses Central Bank Governor Amid Currency Drop
entries.description: Mohammed al-Sudani has dismissed the country’s central bank governor amid growing anger over the weakening of the local currency in recent weeks that has caused the price of food and imports to rise.

entries.title: Russia Presses Attack in Ukraine's South
entries.description: Fighting intensified in Ukraine’s strategically important south, where Moscow claims it is making advances, while Kyiv waits on heavier weapons from its Western allies.
